  "decision_conditions": [
    "The proposed Hub would be an obstruction on the pavement which would result in nuisance and inconvenience to pedestrians at times of busy usage of the footway and it would obstruct highway visibility for approaching vehicles or pedestrians waiting at the bus stop, contrary to Policies DM8 and DM10 of the Kingston Core Strategy (2012), Policies D3 and D8 of the London Plan (2021) and the NPPF (2021).",
    "The proposed Hub would have an overly dominant appearance within the street scene and would detract from the walking environment along High Street and due to its siting in proximity to street furniture would appear as clutter. The Hub is therefore contrary to Policies: CS8 and DM10 of the Kingston Core Strategy (2012), Policy D3 of the London Plan (2021) and the NPPF (2021).",
    "It has not been demonstrated the Hub has been suitably designed to minimise energy consumption in the provision of its services, in accordance with the energy hierarchy, contrary to the NPPF (2021) and Policy SI2 of the London Plan (2021)."
  ],
